   buffer `buf` is only 16 bytes long but is expected to hold potentially up to
   33 bytes, depending on the input `who`. The concatenation operations
   involving `strcpy` and `strcat` do not perform bounds checks, leading to
   buffer overflow when handling large inputs.
   
